               <p>PETER SONTAG. I let out my house in lodgings, and the prisoner was a lodger of mine; he had a whole bed for one night for sixpence; there were three beds in the room; there was only one man sleeping in the same room. The prisoner went away about half past six; and after he was gone, the two sheets and the bed-curtain were missing.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18160918-66-person583">
                  JOHN 
                  NEALE
